      "body" : "For belt-and-suspenders sanity, I think places where we rely on other methods to set state.Invalid should have asserts; e.g.:\r\n\r\n    // Check it again in case a previous version let a bad block in                                                     \r\n    if (!CheckBlock(state, !fJustCheck, !fJustCheck))\r\n    {\r\n        assert(!state.IsValid()); // Rely on CheckBlock to set invalid state\r\n        return false;\r\n    }",
